Help Type: command
Command: wikigraph <archive-uri>/chapter/tree

chapter tree

Purpose:
  Get or set the complete chapter tree.

Usage:
  wikigraph <archive-uri>/chapter/tree get [--json] [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  wikigraph <archive-uri>/chapter/tree set [--input <path>] [--dry-run] [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]

Tree JSON shape:
  `get` without `--json` prints a readable tree. Add `--json` when you need editable tree JSON.

  {
    "chapters": [
      {
        "id": 1,
        "title": "Part I",
        "children": [
          { "id": 2, "title": null, "children": [] }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }

Apply rules:
  - Every existing chapter id must appear exactly once.
  - Unknown, duplicated, or missing chapter ids are rejected.
  - `children` is required on every node.
  - `title` is optional when setting the tree.
  - Omitted `title` means keep the current title.
  - `title: "text"` sets or replaces the chapter title.
  - `title: null` clears the chapter title.
  - Extra fields are rejected.
  - Applying a tree never creates chapters, deletes chapters, or edits source, graph, or summary data.

Dry run:
  `--dry-run` validates the input and prints moved, renamed, and unchanged counts without changing the archive.

Examples:
  wikigraph wkg://book.wikg/chapter/tree get
  wikigraph wkg://book.wikg/chapter/tree get --json > tree.json
  wikigraph wkg://book.wikg/chapter/tree set --input tree.json --dry-run
  wikigraph wkg://book.wikg/chapter/tree set --input tree.json

See also:
  - wikigraph wkg://book.wikg/chapter/3 move --help
  - wikigraph wkg://book.wikg/chapter/3/title set --help
  - wikigraph help command
